oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Cedarcrest Jamboree - 01-10 - WSM
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Segment of Cedarcrest shoes sponsored radio program Cedarcrest Jamboree, orginally broadcast January 10, year unknown, as stated on cue sheet and label. Featuring Louis Buck (announcer), Carl Smith (host ,announcer), Little Jimmy Dickens (performer), Hal Smith (performer), Johnny Sibert (performer), and Cowboy Copas (performer) on radio station WSM (Nashville, Tenn.)
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Little Jimmy Dickens; Carl Smith; Hal Smith; Johnny Sibert; Cowboy Copas
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Test tones -- Louis Buck announces line-up -- Opening theme -- Opening statement (Louis Buck) -- Louis Buck introduces Carl Smith -- Part Of My Heart Is Missing (Carl Smith) -- Carl Smith introduces Hal Smith -- Sugar In The Guord (Hal Smith fiddle) -- Carl Smith introduces Cowboy Copas -- Cowboy Copas thanks everyone and introduces the song -- Golden Moon (Cowboy Copas) -- Carl Smith introduces Johnny Sibert -- Fort Worth Rag (Johnny Sibert steel guitar) -- Carl Smith introduces the next song -- Your Hearts Too Crowded (Carl Smith) -- Carl Smith introduces Little Jimmy Dickens -- Little Jimmy Dickens tells jokes -- Cold Feet (Little Jimmy Dickens) -- Carl Smith introduces Cowboy Copas -- Cowboy Copas introduces the next song -- I'll Pay The Price (Cowboy Copas) -- Carl Smith introduces the next song -- This World Is Not My Home (Carl Smith) -- Carl Smith introduces Hal Smith -- The Eighth Of January (Hal Smith fiddle) -- Carl Smith introduces Cowboy Copas -- Philipino Baby (Cowboy Copas) -- Closing statement (Carl Smith and Louis Buck) -- Closing theme
